PHONE_REDACTEDT09:PORT:PORT.081367Z	   15 Query	insert into daily_analysis_reports (analysis_confidence,analysis_scope_note,day,executive_summary,generated_at,misconfiguration_signals,system_behavior_analysis,user_behavior_analysis) values ('Confidence is high due to the large volume of data analyzed and consistent patterns observed in user behavior and system performance.','This analysis covers one calendar day (PHONE_REDACTED) and focuses on backend lead submission behavior.','PHONE_REDACTED','On the analyzed day, a total of 255 lead submission attempts were made, resulting in 142 successful submissions and 113 failed submissions, yielding a success ratio of approximately 55.69%. User behavior indicates high activity from EMAIL_REDACTED and EMAIL_REDACTED, with failure ratios of 40.58% and 48.72%, respectively.','PHONE_REDACTED:PORT:PORT.077466','The high percentage of duplicate lead submissions suggests a possible configuration issue related to lead validation or storage.','The system processed all lead submission attempts via the website form, and no rate limit failures or final page-specific failures were observed.','The top two users (EMAIL_REDACTED and EMAIL_REDACTED) accounted for 235 out of the total 255 attempts, with a high failure ratio in both cases. The majority of the failures were due to duplicate lead submissions.')
